OL,3,CGovernment rejects key Brook House
OL,4,Cmistreatment inquiry recommendation
OL,6,FWhen asked for her thoughts on the
OL,7,FGovernment's response to her findings,
OL,8,FMs Eves said: "I am concerned that the
OL,9,Finquiry's recommendations have not
OL,10,Fbeen accepted in full; in particular
OL,11,Fthe recommendation of a 28-day time
OL,12,Flimit on detaining people in
OL,13,Fenvironments designed as prisons.
OL,15,F"As I stated in my report, it is my
OL,16,Fview that the inquiry's
OL,17,Frecommendations need to be implemented
OL,18,Fin order to prevent any repeat of the
OL,19,Fkind of unacceptable mistreatment that
OL,20,Ftook place in Brook House."
